# Frontend Conventions

## Stack
- Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS — no framework (no React, Vue, etc.)
- Server-rendered via Express `res.sendFile()` from `views/`
- Stripe.js for payment forms, client-side fetch for API calls

## Structure
- `views/` — full HTML pages (dashboard, checkout, login, store, shipping, etc.)
- `views/admin/` — admin panel pages
- `public/` — static assets (images, CSS, client JS)
- Inline `<script>` blocks in HTML files handle page-specific logic

## Patterns
- API calls use `fetch()` with `credentials: 'include'` for session cookies
- Cart state managed client-side in JS variables within the page script
- Shipping address forms post JSON to `/api/save-shipping-address`
- Checkout flow: store → addons → shipping → checkout → thankyou
- Backer flow starts at login (PIN or email OTP) → dashboard

## UI/UX
- Modern, clean design with consistent color palette
- Responsive layouts using CSS flexbox/grid
- Toast notifications for user feedback
- Loading states on buttons during async operations
- Form validation both client-side (required fields) and server-side

## Key Pages
- `dashboard.html` — backer hub showing pledge, addons, order status, shipping
- `checkout.html` — Stripe Elements card form, order summary, price breakdown
- `store.html` — product catalog with add-to-cart
- `login.html` — PIN entry or email OTP for backer auth
- `admin/` — admin panel for managing orders, users, and analytics
